# TNA Form 01 layout (approved)

## Document title

Use this exact title in `TNA_FORM_01_TITLE`:

`DOST TNA FORM 01 - APPLICATION FOR TECHNOLOGY NEEDS ASSESSMENT`

Rendered via `FormHeader` → `.tna-form-title` (uppercase via CSS).

## Pagination goals

- Section **titles stay with their content** — no orphaned headings (e.g. BENCHMARK INFORMATION split from its tables).
- **Do not force one section per physical page** — short blocks may share a sheet.
- **Comfortable spacing** — not full-A4 forced height, not cramped flush flow.
- **Keep logical footers** — physical page footers via CSS `@page tna-form-01-sheet` with `counter(page)` / `counter(pages)`; no inline per-section footers.

## Implementation pattern

1. **`FormBlock`** — wraps atomic units with `tna-form-block tna-print-section`.
2. **Primitives** — `FormTextBlock`, `FormAttachmentBlock`, and `FormBorderedPanel` already carry block classes so label + value stay together.
3. **Benchmark** — heading + first bullet in one block; each `BenchmarkBullet` + table/text in its own block.
4. **CSS** (`tnaForm01.css`):
   - `break-inside: avoid` on `.tna-form-block` / `.tna-print-section`
   - `break-after: avoid` on `.tna-form-section-heading`
   - Tables inside blocks: `break-inside: auto` (rows may split if block exceeds one page); `thead` stays `break-inside: avoid`
   - Screen: `12px` block gap, `16px` between logical pages
   - Print: `5mm` block gap; `@page margin: 12mm`
   - **Never** use `break-before: always` on sections (prevents short sections sharing a page).

## Print path

Use in-page print via `printTnaForm01Pdf` (clone to `#tna-form-01-print-root` on `body`). Do not revert to popup `document.write` (freezes on 14 pages).

